oai_dc:dc.dc:title: STATIC AND DYNAMIC LOADS ON THE BOTTOM ROW OF ARMOUR UNITS: A THEORETICAL AND PHYSICAL MODEL STUDY
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: van de Koppel, Michael Alexander
Muilwijk, Michiel
Verhagen, Henk Jan
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: rubble-mound breakwater
static load
dynamic load
bottom row
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A physical model study on the row averaged static and dynamic load on the bottom row of single layer armour units in order to investigate the influence of various parameters such as the number of rows on the slope of a breakwater and the initial relative packing density.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 33 (2012): Proceedings of 33rd Conference on Coastal Engineering, Santander, Spain, 2012; structures.44
